Edward Snowden, the whistleblower for U.S. intelligence services, said he was willing to go to Berlin to testify before the German parliament if the U.S. National Security Agency and its director Keith Alexander did not provide answers about their activities.
German MP Hans-Christian Ströbele met with Snowden in Russia on Thursday, where he enjoys the right of asylum, to discuss his testimony in Germany.
