At the annual conference of the American Academy of Pediatrics held this week in Orlando, Florida, Dr. Paul Kaplowitz, a pedo-endocrinologist, explained that these early physical changes are quite common among young Americans and represent a new norm.
“I spend a lot of time reassuring parents — in general, it doesn’t indicate a rapid shift toward full puberty,” Kaplowitz said.
Clear signs of development, such as budging breasts, hair under the arms and in the pubic area, and body odors, appear earlier in girls.
