“Mobile phones are a real problem, not only because they could eventually create interference with navigational instruments, but because we know, according to the FCC, that they could disrupt mobile relay antennas if used on board,” Rosenker said.
An industry advisory committee set up by the FAA to examine the issue recommended last month that the government authorize a wider use of personal electronic devices.
